HEADWORD: cock-a-leekie
<hw>cock-a-leekie</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <ets>cock</ets> + <ets>leek</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A favorite soup in Scotland, made from a capon highly seasoned, and
boiled with leeks and prunes; -- called also
<altname>cocky-leeky</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

